.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-3::.
There are 6 different nationalities: dutch, egyptian, chinese, colombian, japanese, indonesian
The people use 6 different means of transport: helicopter, jet-ski, quad-bike, taxi, tram, van
1. the dutch is on the left of the person driving the helicopter##1
2. the colombian is the person driving the tram##1
3. the person driving the helicopter is on the left of the person driving the taxi##1
4. the person driving the helicopter is on the left of the japanese##1
5. the chinese is on the far right##1
6. the japanese is between the colombian and the person driving the helicopter##2
7. the person driving the jet-ski is on the far left##1
8. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the colombian##1
9. the egyptian is on the far left##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |  2   |     3      |   4    |     5      |     6     |
| Nationality         | egyptian | dutch | indonesian      | japanese | colombian | chinese      |
| Transport   | jet-ski    | van  | helicopter | taxi   | tram       | quad-bike |

